The paper deals with algorithms and data structures for computing and storing cut values in graphs, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the redundancy factor of various cut counting problems, which is related to the combinatorial structure of the problem and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes data structures for storing cut values, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
